WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:04.629
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

00:04.629 --> 00:07.132
Hey, honey,
we should get going.

00:07.299 --> 00:09.426
Why do dresses never
look as good at home

00:09.426 --> 00:10.343
as they do
in the store?

00:10.343 --> 00:14.597
It's because mannequins
have such great bodies.

00:17.100 --> 00:20.728
I-- I mean, not that you--
Forget it.

00:21.396 --> 00:23.731
Wait, are you
eating ice cream?

00:23.731 --> 00:25.067
Uh-huh.

00:25.067 --> 00:27.944
No, we're going out
to a nice dinner.

00:27.944 --> 00:29.196
Put it back.

00:29.196 --> 00:30.738
All right, Mom.

00:31.698 --> 00:33.658
Hey, honey,
are you okay?

00:33.658 --> 00:36.703
I mean, you sure
you wanna do this tonight?

00:36.703 --> 00:38.163
Of course I do.

00:38.163 --> 00:41.166
There's nothing I want more
than to marry you.

00:41.166 --> 00:42.500
I'm just nervous.

00:42.500 --> 00:43.460
I know, I'm nervous too.

00:43.460 --> 00:46.296
That's why I need
the ice cream.

00:46.296 --> 00:49.132
Come here.

00:49.757 --> 00:50.633
It's your wedding day.

00:50.633 --> 00:52.760
If you want ice cream,
go nuts.

00:52.760 --> 00:54.346
Oh, do we have nuts?

00:54.346 --> 00:56.013
Don't make me
rethink tonight.

00:56.013 --> 00:58.558
Jeff and Audrey
are gonna be surprised, huh?

00:58.558 --> 01:00.602
That's the point
of doing it this way.

01:00.602 --> 01:03.230
Russell ask why
you were leaving work early?

01:03.230 --> 01:04.147
No, I told him
I was sick.

01:04.147 --> 01:06.691
He said the gay guy, Mel from
accounting, was sick too

01:06.691 --> 01:10.862
and then he jumped to some
pretty graphic conclusions.

01:11.696 --> 01:14.199
Where is my dry-cleaning?

01:14.199 --> 01:16.368
I don't know.

01:16.993 --> 01:18.703
Here it is.

01:18.703 --> 01:19.954
Where's my purse?

01:19.954 --> 01:21.914
I don't know.
Oh.

01:21.914 --> 01:22.790
Here it is.

01:22.790 --> 01:25.168
Oh, God. Where's
my cell phone?

01:25.168 --> 01:26.669
I don't know.

01:26.669 --> 01:27.837
Oh. Here it is.

01:27.837 --> 01:30.965
Hey--
Hey! Where's my gun?

01:30.965 --> 01:31.633
What?
Nothing.

01:31.633 --> 01:34.010
I'm just tired
of the old frantic routine

01:34.010 --> 01:35.345
trying to get ready
to go out.

01:35.345 --> 01:36.763
Well, I'm sorry,
I do a little more

01:36.763 --> 01:40.933
than throw on a sport coat
and forget to reapply deodorant.

01:40.933 --> 01:43.270
This restaurant Adam and Jen
are taking us to

01:43.270 --> 01:46.063
is very fancy, and they
don't have a lot of money.

01:46.063 --> 01:47.399
Don't order anything pricey.

01:47.399 --> 01:51.027
I got a hankering
for free lobster.

01:51.027 --> 01:52.404
No lobster.

01:52.404 --> 01:54.406
Fine, I'll eat
that box of Pop-Tarts.

01:54.406 --> 01:57.575
That'll save them
the price of an appetizer.

01:57.575 --> 01:58.951
No, no. We'll just--

01:58.951 --> 02:00.370
We can split a salad.

02:00.370 --> 02:03.665
Oh, can we?

02:04.457 --> 02:07.294
All right.
How do I look?

02:08.002 --> 02:09.587
You know.

02:11.423 --> 02:12.382
Why do I bother?

02:12.382 --> 02:14.091
Yeah, why do you?

02:14.091 --> 02:15.968
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S "HOW MANY WAYS"
PLAYING]

02:15.968 --> 02:20.307
♪♪ How many ways
To say, "I love you?" ♪♪

02:21.391 --> 02:26.563
♪♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared? ♪♪

02:26.563 --> 02:29.191
♪♪ With you by my side ♪♪

02:29.191 --> 02:30.900
♪♪ There is no denyin' ♪♪

02:30.900 --> 02:35.238
♪♪ I can't wait
For me and you ♪♪

02:39.409 --> 02:41.578
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

02:41.578 --> 02:43.120
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

02:43.120 --> 02:47.083
Hey, uh, Jen wanted me to check
to see if you guys are ready.

02:47.083 --> 02:48.251
I am. Audrey's not.

02:48.251 --> 02:49.877
Well, can you push her along?

02:49.877 --> 02:51.213
"Can I push her along"?

02:51.213 --> 02:53.631
It's just that tonight
is kind of important,

02:53.631 --> 02:55.174
and we sort
of have a schedule.

02:55.174 --> 02:57.635
All right, you wanna try?
Go in.

03:01.223 --> 03:03.725
[AUDREY SCREAMS]

03:04.309 --> 03:05.685
Dude. Dude, dude,

03:05.685 --> 03:07.854
she's-- She's wearing
her underwear.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.689
Why the hell did you
send him in there?

03:09.689 --> 03:12.234
You were just dressed.
What happened?

03:12.234 --> 03:13.235
I decided to change.

03:13.235 --> 03:17.071
Can you ever, for once in your
whole life ever just be helpful?

03:17.071 --> 03:18.698
You want helpful?
Okay, how's this?

03:18.698 --> 03:22.494
You look the same in everything,
I'm hungry, hurry up.

03:23.828 --> 03:26.289
You are such an ass.

03:26.289 --> 03:27.915
Maybe we just
shouldn't even go.

03:27.915 --> 03:29.667
Oh, no.
Then I wouldn't get

03:29.667 --> 03:33.546
to not have lobster
and half a salad.

03:35.465 --> 03:36.007
[JEFF SIGHS]

03:36.007 --> 03:37.759
Dude, why don't you
go without us.

03:37.759 --> 03:42.222
She's about to turn green
and bust out of her clothes.

03:43.097 --> 03:44.266
She's the Hulk.

03:44.266 --> 03:46.893
Look, you have
to come with us tonight.

03:46.893 --> 03:47.894
Why?

03:47.894 --> 03:50.938
Well, there's a special
secret reason.

03:50.938 --> 03:52.064
I don't care.

03:52.064 --> 03:52.732
Okay, okay, okay.

03:52.732 --> 03:55.443
Okay, only if you promise
not to tell Audrey.

03:55.443 --> 03:57.654
I promise.
Okay.

03:57.654 --> 03:59.947
Tonight, before we go
to the restaurant,

03:59.947 --> 04:01.408
we are going
to City Hall.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.909
Jen and I
are getting married.

04:02.909 --> 04:05.995
Oh! Good for you, buddy.
Yeah. Yeah?

04:05.995 --> 04:08.831
Oh, yeah. Right.
Oh! Jesus.

04:08.831 --> 04:10.542
[LAUGHS]

04:16.213 --> 04:18.383
We're holding hands now.

04:19.175 --> 04:19.801
Yeah.

04:19.801 --> 04:21.844
Anyway, that's why
I wanted you to go.

04:21.844 --> 04:24.264
Why'd you guys
decide to do it now?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.932
Jen's parents have been
pressuring her

04:25.932 --> 04:29.143
to have this big wedding,
and tell Jen to do one thing,

04:29.143 --> 04:30.144
she's gonna
do the other.

04:30.144 --> 04:33.356
I didn't know Audrey
was selling franchises.

04:33.356 --> 04:35.232
Count us in.
Great.

04:35.232 --> 04:38.528
Oh, remember,
don't tell Audrey.

04:38.528 --> 04:39.737
You got it.

04:39.737 --> 04:41.113
They're getting married?

04:41.113 --> 04:41.698
Tonight?
Yes.

04:41.698 --> 04:44.451
And we're the witnesses but
we're not supposed to know?

04:44.451 --> 04:47.954
Excellent repeating
of everything I just said.

04:47.954 --> 04:48.746
Oh, my God. I...

04:48.746 --> 04:51.499
I don't know what to say.
I-- I didn't expect this.

04:51.499 --> 04:53.167
You didn't win
an Oscar, Audrey.

04:53.167 --> 04:55.670
Well, I have to change
into something nicer.

04:55.670 --> 04:56.754
I mean,
I am the maid of honor.

04:56.754 --> 05:01.175
You're married, so actually
you are the matron of honor.

05:01.175 --> 05:04.554
You need to change too.
[SIGHS]

05:04.554 --> 05:05.137
Why?

05:05.137 --> 05:09.851
Because it's just us,
so you're like the best man.

05:09.851 --> 05:12.228
Boy, that's crazy ironic.

05:13.730 --> 05:16.273
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

05:16.399 --> 05:20.152
Hello, there. One large chicken
noodle soup to go, please.

05:20.152 --> 05:20.778
Anything else?

05:20.778 --> 05:22.614
No, no, just the soup today,
thank you.

05:22.614 --> 05:24.073
My friend's
not feeling well, see?

05:24.073 --> 05:28.160
Chicken soup won't cure
what he's spreading around.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.913
Oh, no, no, no.
It's for Adam.

05:30.913 --> 05:34.125
FYI, I'm on some experimental
pills from Mexico

05:34.125 --> 05:37.795
and so far, so bueno.

05:38.212 --> 05:39.130
Dude, you have to do this?

05:39.130 --> 05:41.090
We're gonna be late
for the movie.

05:41.090 --> 05:42.133
I don't have to, I want to.

05:42.133 --> 05:43.885
Mr. Rhodes left work
feeling sick.

05:43.885 --> 05:45.678
Some nice hot soup
will do him well.

05:45.678 --> 05:47.597
I mean, I could understand
if you want

05:47.597 --> 05:49.391
to have sex
with the guy, but...

05:49.391 --> 05:52.143
Wait, do you want
to have sex with the guy?

05:52.143 --> 05:54.562
I'm just being
a good friend.

05:54.562 --> 05:55.438
If you were a better friend,

05:55.438 --> 05:58.232
maybe people would invite
you out more often. Hm?

05:58.232 --> 06:00.985
You ever consider that?
Hm?

06:00.985 --> 06:02.111
I get invited out plenty.

06:02.111 --> 06:07.366
Being asked to leave doesn't
count as being invited out.

06:09.118 --> 06:10.745
Okay,
everything's on track,

06:10.745 --> 06:12.955
Jeff and Audrey
are just about ready.

06:12.955 --> 06:14.707
Does this dress
look good on me?

06:14.707 --> 06:15.750
Yeah,
it looks great.

06:15.750 --> 06:17.419
No it doesn't.
You're insane.

06:17.419 --> 06:19.378
Okay,
it doesn't look great.

06:19.378 --> 06:22.381
Oh, don't bother.
Your opinion is useless.

06:22.381 --> 06:25.760
I'm gonna go ask Audrey.

06:26.428 --> 06:28.763
Yay, I get that forever.

06:31.933 --> 06:35.269
Where's Audrey? I want to ask
her how I look in this dress.

06:35.269 --> 06:37.063
You look fine.
Shut up.

06:37.063 --> 06:40.817
Audrey is definitively
selling franchises.

06:43.194 --> 06:43.945
Hey.

06:43.945 --> 06:45.863
Oh. You changed.
You look nice.

06:45.863 --> 06:48.700
Well, how gay of you
to notice.

06:48.700 --> 06:51.828
Hey, Jen. Oh, I am
so excited about tonight.

06:51.828 --> 06:53.830
Me too. What do you think
of this dress?

06:53.830 --> 06:57.917
Uh, not great on the boobs,
even worse on the arms.

06:57.917 --> 06:58.918
Thank you.

06:58.918 --> 07:01.128
Couldn't just do that,
could you?

07:01.128 --> 07:05.550
Fine. Your legs
look weird too.

07:09.345 --> 07:09.971
No, but I--

07:09.971 --> 07:12.056
Just go.
I was trying to say--

07:12.056 --> 07:13.600
But--

07:15.101 --> 07:16.894
[JIGGLING DOORKNOB]

07:16.894 --> 07:17.437
Give me the key.

07:17.437 --> 07:21.733
Oh, hold on,
I left it inside.

07:23.526 --> 07:24.777
He locked us out.

07:24.777 --> 07:29.532
Oh. These are the times
I wish I'd learned magic.

07:29.532 --> 07:33.620
Oh, my God, so now I have no
boobs, giant arms, weird legs.

07:33.620 --> 07:34.370
I can't go out like this.

07:34.370 --> 07:37.289
People will think
I am a transvestite.

07:37.582 --> 07:39.834
That will not
reflect well on me.

07:39.834 --> 07:41.628
All right. Calm down.

07:41.628 --> 07:43.796
You can borrow
something of mine.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.465
Thank you.

07:46.883 --> 07:51.053
So you've been dealing with this
getting-ready-to-go-out drama

07:51.053 --> 07:52.013
for, like, 14 years?

07:52.013 --> 07:53.598
Oh, yeah.
How do you handle it?

07:53.598 --> 07:58.269
I have developed a pretty
effective method. I'll show you.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.900
Want me to show you again?

08:04.275 --> 08:05.818
No, it's okay.
I got it.

08:05.818 --> 08:08.362
I'm gonna show you again.

08:11.407 --> 08:13.743
Oh. Hey, uh, didn't we
give you a spare key

08:13.743 --> 08:16.287
the time we went
out of town a while back?

08:16.287 --> 08:17.288
You sure did.

08:17.288 --> 08:18.455
I never told you this,

08:18.455 --> 08:22.669
but that week
Audrey had me use your toilet.

08:22.669 --> 08:25.212
Anyway, I-- I can't remember
if it was before

08:25.212 --> 08:26.213
or after we changed our lock,

08:26.213 --> 08:28.966
but could you get the key?
I'll give it a try.

08:28.966 --> 08:30.134
Yeah.
You still have

08:30.134 --> 08:33.930
that bottle of Scotch that
I gave you for your birthday?

08:33.930 --> 08:34.889
Yeah.
All right.

08:34.889 --> 08:36.933
If this key works,
bring it back.

08:36.933 --> 08:38.100
But that was a gift.

08:38.100 --> 08:41.938
Look, you had it for three
weeks, it's public domain.

08:44.440 --> 08:46.483
Stupid key.

08:46.483 --> 08:47.610
[JIGGLES DOORKNOB]

08:47.610 --> 08:49.821
Dumb door.

08:51.698 --> 08:52.574
Mr. Rhodes?

08:52.574 --> 08:54.534
Oh, hey, Timmy. Russell.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.160
I thought you were sick.

08:56.160 --> 08:57.369
[COUGHS]
I am.

08:57.369 --> 08:59.789
Why are you
all dressed up?

08:59.789 --> 09:01.415
Okay, Russell,
you were right.

09:01.415 --> 09:05.502
I'm going out with Mel
from accounting.

09:08.255 --> 09:10.967
All right, worst liar ever,
what's going on?

09:10.967 --> 09:12.093
I can't tell you.

09:12.093 --> 09:14.929
Really? What if I just stare
at you like this?

09:14.929 --> 09:16.138
Okay, okay, okay.

09:16.138 --> 09:17.264
I'll tell you the truth.

09:17.264 --> 09:19.601
Jen and I are going out
with Jeff and Audrey.

09:19.601 --> 09:22.061
Hm. Doesn't seem
that clandestine.

09:22.061 --> 09:25.272
Yeah, if clandestine
means not boring.

09:25.272 --> 09:26.649
What's the big cover-up?

09:26.649 --> 09:30.570
Well, before dinner, um...

09:30.570 --> 09:34.490
we are having
an intervention.

09:34.490 --> 09:36.075
For Jeff's drinking.

09:36.075 --> 09:38.995
Makes sense.
No surprise there.

09:38.995 --> 09:41.455
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

09:42.957 --> 09:44.959
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

09:45.668 --> 09:47.795
All right,
what about this one?

09:47.795 --> 09:48.420
Whoa.

09:48.420 --> 09:51.758
I don't know.
It's a little dated.

09:51.758 --> 09:54.385
Oh. Yeah, that one has been
in there a while.

09:54.385 --> 09:55.427
The tags are still on.

09:55.427 --> 09:59.682
Yeah. I-- I bought it years ago
and never wore it.

09:59.682 --> 10:01.100
This store
opened last month.

10:01.100 --> 10:03.185
Okay. Would you
just pick a dress?

10:03.185 --> 10:06.480
Well, I don't know
about any of these.

10:06.480 --> 10:09.275
Well, then stick
with what you have on.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.317
It looks great.

10:10.317 --> 10:12.904
And we can hide it
with a shawl.

10:12.904 --> 10:14.071
No, no, I can't!

10:14.071 --> 10:15.364
Tonight's just
too important.

10:15.364 --> 10:20.953
I know. I mean its dinner.
It's a very important meal.

10:21.663 --> 10:22.997
I guess.

10:23.623 --> 10:28.502
There is actually one dress
I think would work for me.

10:28.502 --> 10:30.296
Okay, good. Which one?
Well, actually,

10:30.296 --> 10:34.216
it's the one you're wearing.
I've always loved it.

10:34.550 --> 10:35.968
Oh, but--
No, you're right.

10:35.968 --> 10:39.555
Forget it,
it's way too much to ask.

10:39.889 --> 10:41.641
No. You know what?
It isn't.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.018
Here, unzip me.

10:45.311 --> 10:50.357
Yes, unzip her.

10:52.359 --> 10:53.152
What are you doing?

10:53.152 --> 10:56.113
I was on my way to the bathroom
when I stumbled

10:56.113 --> 10:59.075
upon this delightful
tableau.

11:01.035 --> 11:03.913
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

11:04.205 --> 11:08.209
Big surprise we weren't invited
to Mr. Bingham's intervention,

11:08.209 --> 11:10.252
thank you very much.

11:10.419 --> 11:13.255
Why do you wanna go
to an intervention anyway?

11:13.255 --> 11:16.801
Are they serving
chicken tikka masala?

11:17.384 --> 11:18.594
No.

11:19.345 --> 11:21.388
Lamb?

11:22.514 --> 11:24.600
No. I would want to do it
to help a friend.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.518
But thanks
to my association with you,

11:26.518 --> 11:28.270
I'm excluded from doing
something of value

11:28.270 --> 11:31.774
and instead am going to see...
What film did you choose again?

11:31.774 --> 11:33.609
Stewardess School Blues.
Ugh.

11:33.609 --> 11:35.027
Stewardess School Blues.

11:35.027 --> 11:39.824
Sounds in keeping with your
"no booby, no watchy" policy.

11:39.824 --> 11:42.618
Yeah, I guess it's about a bunch
of chicks who are studying

11:42.618 --> 11:45.997
to be stewardesses and then
they get sad about something.

11:45.997 --> 11:49.166
But you gotta figure
they get cheered up, right?

11:49.166 --> 11:52.044
I don't care.
I don't want to see it.

11:52.044 --> 11:55.089
In fact, we're not
going to see a movie.

11:55.089 --> 11:55.923
[PUNCHES BUTTON]

11:55.923 --> 11:58.259
We're going back
to help our friends.

11:58.259 --> 11:59.051
Oh, come on.

11:59.051 --> 12:03.097
It got three stars
from Boing.com.

12:03.806 --> 12:05.016
They're though.

12:05.016 --> 12:06.893
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

12:06.893 --> 12:08.727
All right, I think
we're all ready.

12:08.727 --> 12:11.230
Whoa, look at you.
You look smoking hot.

12:11.230 --> 12:13.440
I mean,
really gorgeous.

12:13.440 --> 12:16.568
Um, that's
my dress, Jeff.

12:16.568 --> 12:19.321
Not anymore.

12:19.488 --> 12:21.824
All right. How do I
look in this one?

12:21.824 --> 12:23.951
You know.

12:25.787 --> 12:28.330
That was really rude, Jeff.

12:28.330 --> 12:30.792
But thank you.

12:31.125 --> 12:32.960
What did you say,
beer?

12:32.960 --> 12:35.671
Why, yes,
I will come and drink you.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.256
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

12:40.009 --> 12:41.385
What are you guys
doing here?

12:41.385 --> 12:44.763
I don't know.
Ask the Indian Mr. Rogers.

12:47.099 --> 12:50.019
Mr. Rhodes, now I realize
we weren't invited,

12:50.019 --> 12:53.355
but I'd like to offer
my help as a friend.

12:53.355 --> 12:56.192
[WHISPERING]
With the intervention.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.779
[WHISPERING]
With the what?

13:02.031 --> 13:04.158
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
The intervention?

13:04.158 --> 13:05.784
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Oh, yeah. That.

13:05.784 --> 13:09.038
Yes, I'll have you know, I have
experience in this matters.

13:09.038 --> 13:11.040
In fact, I facilitated
an intervention

13:11.040 --> 13:14.251
back in my days
at the university.

13:14.251 --> 13:17.504
Man, you have
a sick vocabulary.

13:17.504 --> 13:18.422
Yeah, yeah.

13:18.422 --> 13:20.341
I bet you're great
at that, um...

13:20.341 --> 13:23.094
What's that game
with all the words?

13:24.511 --> 13:25.888
Scrabble?

13:25.888 --> 13:28.432
Hey, you're the word guy.

13:33.437 --> 13:34.355
Hey.
Hey.

13:34.355 --> 13:35.772
What are you doing here?

13:35.772 --> 13:37.900
Me and Timmy
just stopped by.

13:37.900 --> 13:41.112
You know,
as friends will do.

13:42.154 --> 13:42.989
So going to dinner?

13:42.989 --> 13:45.867
Well, it's not really
just dinner.

13:46.742 --> 13:47.701
Oh, you know?

13:47.701 --> 13:49.954
Yeah. Yeah.

13:49.954 --> 13:50.913
Do you?

13:50.913 --> 13:52.748
Yeah.

13:52.748 --> 13:53.916
And you're cool
with it?

13:53.916 --> 13:56.710
To the extent
that I give a crap.

13:57.419 --> 14:00.923
We all knew it was gonna happen
sooner or later.

14:01.798 --> 14:04.593
Huh. Well, uh, you think
it'll make a difference?

14:04.593 --> 14:07.889
Nah, nothing's
gonna change.

14:07.889 --> 14:10.724
It'll be a big to-do,
Audrey'll cry.

14:10.933 --> 14:14.270
Then it's right back
to the same old same old.

14:14.686 --> 14:18.024
Jeff, wait. You really think
you should be drinking--

14:18.024 --> 14:20.109
Ooh, Pop-Tarts.

14:20.317 --> 14:23.362
All right. Oh, great,
we are all finally ready.

14:23.362 --> 14:24.196
Let's hit it.

14:24.196 --> 14:26.115
Yeah, but first,
a toast.

14:26.115 --> 14:29.076
A-- A toast?

14:29.994 --> 14:31.954
Yeah. Jeff,
do we have some champagne?

14:31.954 --> 14:36.000
I may have a bottle
hidden away somewhere.

14:36.000 --> 14:38.002
[CHUCKLES]
I bet you do.

14:38.002 --> 14:39.336
Go get it.

14:39.336 --> 14:40.046
[LAUGHS]

14:40.046 --> 14:42.173
Mrs. Bingham, are you sure
this is wise?

14:42.173 --> 14:44.091
Wise?
Who cares about wise?

14:44.091 --> 14:45.551
Let's get our drink on,
Timmy.

14:45.551 --> 14:48.304
Mrs. Bingham,
you're enabling him.

14:48.304 --> 14:51.390
Um, actually,
I'm enabling all of us

14:51.390 --> 14:53.184
to have a really
good time.

14:53.184 --> 14:53.893
[LAUGHS]

14:53.893 --> 14:58.189
Jeff gets really grouchy
if he loses his buzz.

14:59.023 --> 15:00.691
I found a bottle.

15:00.942 --> 15:03.819
But what's everybody else
gonna drink?

15:03.819 --> 15:06.113
[ALL LAUGH]

15:06.405 --> 15:08.950
Mr. Rhodes, I don't understand
what's happening here.

15:08.950 --> 15:12.369
Oh, he's saying he's gonna drink
the whole bottle himself.

15:12.369 --> 15:15.872
No, what I meant was--
Okay, look, never mind.

15:15.872 --> 15:17.124
All right, listen up.

15:17.124 --> 15:20.627
We all know what's really
happening tonight.

15:20.627 --> 15:21.170
They do?

15:21.170 --> 15:22.088
Adam,
did you tell them?

15:22.088 --> 15:24.173
Yes, he did.
And it's a good thing I came,

15:24.173 --> 15:27.759
because you're all
shockingly bad at this.

15:29.595 --> 15:30.137
So if I may.

15:30.137 --> 15:34.225
Mr. Bingham,
this is an intervention.

15:34.225 --> 15:39.188
Your drinking
is destroying your life.

15:39.688 --> 15:42.191
You're hurting yourself,
those closest to you,

15:42.191 --> 15:44.318
and I want you to know
we are all here tonight

15:44.318 --> 15:47.488
to confront you
with love and compassion.

15:47.488 --> 15:48.864
Everyone.

15:54.453 --> 15:56.747
Everyone.

15:58.790 --> 16:00.126
Still just me?

16:00.126 --> 16:02.086
Hey, what the hell
is going on?

16:02.086 --> 16:04.755
Okay, okay,
here's what happened.

16:04.755 --> 16:06.590
Timmy, get off Jeff.

16:07.341 --> 16:09.385
[SIGHS]
I ran into Russell and Timmy,

16:09.385 --> 16:12.679
and in order to not tell them
we're getting married tonight,

16:12.679 --> 16:15.141
I told them we are
having an intervention.

16:15.141 --> 16:18.269
Oh, I'd buy that.
Good thinking.

16:18.769 --> 16:20.437
You're getting
married tonight?

16:20.437 --> 16:22.481
Yeah,
I'm the maid of honor.

16:22.481 --> 16:25.234
Matron.
How about widow?

16:25.234 --> 16:27.819
You told Audrey?
No, I only told Jeff.

16:27.819 --> 16:29.571
I told.
You weren't supposed to.

16:29.571 --> 16:31.198
You weren't supposed
to tell me.

16:31.198 --> 16:34.201
You weren't supposed
to tell anybody.

16:37.246 --> 16:39.540
Congrats, though.

16:39.706 --> 16:42.168
So, what are you
going to wear?

16:43.085 --> 16:45.421
Okay, that's it.
You know--

16:45.421 --> 16:47.256
This was supposed to be
a fun surprise,

16:47.256 --> 16:49.175
but the night's is
turning into a disaster.

16:49.175 --> 16:52.053
I'm not wearing my own dress,
Adam has ice cream on his tie.

16:52.053 --> 16:55.097
Not from tonight, though,
just to defend myself.

16:55.097 --> 16:56.098
And if you think about it,

16:56.098 --> 16:57.891
why do we even
have to do this at all?

16:57.891 --> 17:00.227
What do you mean?
We love each other.

17:00.227 --> 17:01.312
We have a great thing.

17:01.312 --> 17:04.940
Why do we have to go through all
the trouble to make it official?

17:04.940 --> 17:08.319
Who cares?
I know I don't.

17:11.530 --> 17:12.198
Are you sure?

17:12.198 --> 17:15.326
I'm 100 percent sure
I do not care.

17:15.326 --> 17:17.619
Let's just go home.

17:17.619 --> 17:18.620
Okay.

17:18.620 --> 17:19.788
Well, um...

17:19.788 --> 17:22.374
I guess we're just gonna
call it a night.

17:22.374 --> 17:23.209
Hold on a second here.

17:23.209 --> 17:26.920
We're not just gonna
call it a night.

17:26.920 --> 17:29.881
You wanna have
the intervention?

17:30.549 --> 17:32.051
No. Look,

17:32.051 --> 17:36.222
maybe this is the Scotch
talking, or possibly the beer,

17:36.222 --> 17:39.683
or the wine cooler I found
in my sports bag this morning.

17:39.683 --> 17:42.728
Guys, are we sure we don't
want this intervention?

17:42.728 --> 17:46.898
Look, I think that you guys
should get married tonight.

17:46.898 --> 17:48.234
Maybe I'm old-fashioned,

17:48.234 --> 17:50.194
but I think people
who are living together

17:50.194 --> 17:52.863
should be married.
You feel different. You know?

17:52.863 --> 17:55.366
You become a team,
working together.

17:55.366 --> 17:58.619
He's right. It's like--
Audrey, not now, please.

17:58.619 --> 18:01.497
You guys both know
what a pain in the ass it is

18:01.497 --> 18:03.665
to meet somebody
and get them to like you.

18:03.665 --> 18:05.584
You guys are lucky
that you found each other.

18:05.584 --> 18:09.505
So let's just lock this in
and do it, and stop annoying me.

18:09.505 --> 18:13.509
I'm kind of on Jeff's side.
You know what, Audrey? Please.

18:13.509 --> 18:14.426
[SIGHS]

18:14.426 --> 18:16.428
Can we still make it
to City Hall in time?

18:16.428 --> 18:19.390
Well, it's gonna be tight,
but we can make it.

18:19.390 --> 18:21.517
Let's go.

18:22.393 --> 18:23.852
Aye, aye, aye.

18:23.852 --> 18:24.978
See, sir?
[SIGHS]

18:24.978 --> 18:26.522
Doesn't helping friends
feel better

18:26.522 --> 18:30.776
than watching jiggly flight
attendants bounce up and down?

18:31.985 --> 18:35.156
I feel I've answered
my own question.

18:35.156 --> 18:36.907
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:36.907 --> 18:37.908
To Adam and Jen.

18:37.908 --> 18:40.369
Yeah!
Cheers!

18:40.911 --> 18:43.539
And I wanna thank Jeff
for making the great speech

18:43.539 --> 18:45.957
that pushed us to follow
through with our plan

18:45.957 --> 18:47.834
to get married tonight.
It's ironic.

18:47.834 --> 18:50.129
If he hadn't take
so much time with his speech,

18:50.129 --> 18:53.674
we might have made it
to City Hall in time.

18:53.674 --> 18:55.342
But if he hadn't
made the speech,

18:55.342 --> 18:57.636
you wouldn't even
have tried to...

18:57.636 --> 18:58.429
Never mind.

18:58.429 --> 19:02.057
Well, I'm happy. This just
buys Adam more time to bail.

19:02.057 --> 19:03.392
Not gonna happen, buddy.

19:03.392 --> 19:06.353
Well, that's what my dad said
when I asked him

19:06.353 --> 19:08.355
if he was gonna bail
on my mom.

19:08.355 --> 19:10.149
And, sure enough--

19:10.149 --> 19:12.234
[SOBS]

19:12.693 --> 19:16.530
Maybe next time you'll decide
to have a real wedding.

19:16.530 --> 19:17.739
That was a good day.

19:17.739 --> 19:19.074
Aw.
This one here,

19:19.074 --> 19:20.701
she looked
like a movie star.

19:20.701 --> 19:22.328
Oh.
[AUDREY CHUCKLES]

19:22.328 --> 19:25.997
You see? All of you
who constantly ask me, "why?"

19:25.997 --> 19:27.708
Every so often
he steps up.

19:27.708 --> 19:31.253
I didn't say
what movie star.

19:31.753 --> 19:32.671
That's okay, Jeff.

19:32.671 --> 19:36.258
Ernest Borgnine's
a movie star.

19:36.258 --> 19:36.675
Shut up.

19:36.675 --> 19:41.638
Okay, I've got four Diet Cokes,
one lemonade and a Scotch rocks.

19:41.638 --> 19:44.933
Scotch? Who knew
the diner served booze?

19:44.933 --> 19:47.186
I did.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.896
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

19:51.690 --> 19:53.317
But we didn't
even get married.

19:53.317 --> 19:54.860
I know,
I just want to practice

19:54.860 --> 19:56.612
carrying you
across the threshold.

19:56.612 --> 19:58.655
Good thing the super
had another key.

19:58.655 --> 20:00.366
All right,
here it goes.

20:00.366 --> 20:01.617
Oh! God.

20:01.617 --> 20:03.369
All right.
It's not working.

20:03.369 --> 20:06.079
Hold on.
Oh!

20:06.079 --> 20:08.915
Okay! Stop it! Put me down!
Okay.

20:08.915 --> 20:11.460
[JEN SCREAMS]
[BODY THUDS TO FLOOR]

20:11.460 --> 20:13.920
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:15.422 --> 20:17.383
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
